headline.main: SCOTT FITZGERALD, AUTHOR, DIES AT 44; Writer of 'The Great Gatsby' and 'This Side of Paradise' Interpreted 'Jazz Era' STRICKEN IN HOLLYWOOD Brilliant Novelist of Twenties, Inactive Recently, Likened Self to 'Cracked Plate'

snippet: HOLLYWOOD, Calif., Dec. 22 (AP) --F. Scott Fitzgerald, novelist, short story writer and scenarist, died at his Hollywood home yesterday. His age was 44. He suffered a heart attack three weeks ago.
